---
description: Implementation rules for the signtraker Python API client project.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
Implement runtime code under `./signtraker/` and group endpoints by resource or
service boundary (one module + one client class per group).

Use Google-style docstrings and thorough type hints for generated Python.
The auth header value is `Authorization: ST-API {api_key}`.

Every endpoint or client change must update:
- tests under `./tests/`
- docs under `./docs/`
- examples under `./examples/` when user-facing usage changes
- the owning planning docs under `docs/planning/signtraker-api-client/`

Do not mark an endpoint complete until code, tests, docs, and status docs all
land.
